{
  "texts": [
    "The literature has evolved along several methodological lines to address it.",
    "Two broad classes of estimation strategies have become particularly prominent:• Two-Stage Least-Squares (2SLS).",
    "This classical approach and its various generalizations involves a sequential estimation procedure.",
    "Typically, the first stage estimates the conditional expectation of the endogenous variable (or its features) given the instrument, and the second stage uses these predictions to estimate the structural function.",
    "• Saddle-point optimization."
  ]
}